# TODO.4 — ASR Transcription Node

## Objective

Implement `src/asr_transcribe.py` — WhisperX transcription with word-level timestamps, confidence, and speaker diarization.

## Tasks

1. Implement `run(audio: AudioMeta, config: JobConfig) -> list[ASRSegment]`:
   - Load WhisperX model (configurable size: tiny/base/small/medium/large)
   - Transcribe audio
   - Align words to get word-level timestamps
   - Run speaker diarization (optional, controlled by config)
   - Flag low-confidence words (threshold configurable, default 0.6)
   - Flag segments with quality issues: low_confidence, possible_term_error, long_silence
2. Map WhisperX output to `ASRSegment` schema
3. Write `tests/test_asr_transcribe.py`:
   - Mock WhisperX model and alignment
   - Test segment generation from mock output
   - Test low-confidence flagging logic
   - Test speaker label assignment

## Acceptance Criteria

- Produces list of ASRSegment with word-level timestamps
- Low-confidence words flagged correctly
- Speaker IDs assigned when diarization enabled
- Tests pass without GPU or WhisperX model

## Dependencies

- TODO.1, TODO.2, TODO.3

## Notes

- WhisperX requires a HuggingFace token for pyannote speaker diarization
- Model size should be configurable to allow fast testing with tiny model
